Company Overview of Mizuho Bank, Ltd.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
As of July 1, 2013, Mizuho Bank, Ltd. was acquired by Mizuho Bank, Ltd. Mizuho Bank, Ltd. provides various banking and financial products and services for corporations, financial institutions, individuals, public sector entities, and small and medium-sized enterprises in Japan and internationally. The company offers deposit products, including current, ordinary, time, specified, nonresident, foreign currency, and negotiable time deposits; deposits at notice; and deposits for tax. It also provides lending products, such as loans by bill, loans on deed, and overdrafts; and discounts for bills and bank acceptances, commercial papers, and documentary bills. In addition, the company is involved i...
As of July 1, 2013, Mizuho Bank, Ltd. was acquired by Mizuho Bank, Ltd. Mizuho Bank, Ltd. provides various banking and financial products and services for corporations, financial institutions, individuals, public sector entities, and small and medium-sized enterprises in Japan and internationally. The company offers deposit products, including current, ordinary, time, specified, nonresident, foreign currency, and negotiable time deposits; deposits at notice; and deposits for tax. It also provides lending products, such as loans by bill, loans on deed, and overdrafts; and discounts for bills and bank acceptances, commercial papers, and documentary bills. In addition, the company is involved in buying and selling securities and government bonds; investment in government bonds, corporate bonds, stocks, and other securities for deposit payout reserve and fund management; and provision of exchange for remittance, credit to current accounts, and money collection services. Further, it provides various foreign exchange services related to imports, exports, and foreign remittance; corporate bond trustee and management trustee services; and agency services for public bond subscriptions, register of public bonds, etc. Additionally, the company acts as a receiving agent for payment for shares, as well as paying agent for stock dividends, and public bond principals and interests; an agent for the Organization worker's Retirement Allowance Mutual Aid, etc.; and provides agency loans on behalf of public sector financial institutions. It also offers safekeeping and safe deposit, securities lending, debt guarantee, public bond underwriting, lottery, trust agent, consulting, and pension administrative services; sells securities investment trusts; buys and sells gold; handles commercial papers; sells insurance policies; and provides interest rate and currency derivatives, and other derivatives. The company was founded in 2002 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
Detailed Description


